content.description: Start sitting on sidepull huecos, made a big move up and left to a big jug, move out onto the undercling on the roof. Avoid the large detached looking block while you go up and right onto the slab top out.
content.location: On the right side of the overhang.

content.description: This problem follows the obvious line of good holds up the left side of the overhang. Start sitting (laying) on the lowest possible holds at the bottom of the overhang. Please let me know the real name of this route if you know it so I can update this page.
content.location: Left side of the North Of The Chains Overhang.

content.description: Start matched on the far right side of the boulder. Make a move up right to a sloping side pull, then work your feet so you can stab backward to the good left hand undercling. Reach back right hand to a good side-pull pinch, set a knee bar and fire for the crimps at the lip. The top out is no gimme, so keep it together.
content.protection: A few pads and someone to make sure you don't brain your head on the rock to the right.
content.location: Far right side of the north overhang boulder.

content.description: This steep overhang is located between the lower set of chains and the dam by Sign Of The Cross and features several good problems not listed in the Wilder guidebook.
